place.name: GAMRIE
place.gazetteerText: Gamrie, coast par., Banffshire, 17,041 ac., pop. 6756; contains Macduff; the ruins of the ancient church (St John's; said to have been founded 1004) are at the head of Gamrie Bay, # mile W. of Gardenstown. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)
